## Installation

### Download from the App Store (iPhone and iPad)

1. Open the App Store on your iPhone or iPad.
2. Search for "PDF Language Translator" in the search bar.
3. Tap on the app icon in the search results.
4. On the app page, tap the "Get" or "Download" button.
5. Authenticate with your Apple ID, if prompted.
6. Wait for the app to download and install on your device.
7. Once installed, the app icon will appear on your home screen.

## Features

PDF Language Translator offers a range of features to translate, Manage, View and share your PDF Files. your all-in-one solution for a clutter-free and efficient document experience. 
Explore the following capabilities:

### PDF Translator

PDF Translator appears on the first page with a box where you need to browse the PDF File from your device using browse button. Please select a PDF in English. Select your language pack to translate. Afterward, click 'download' if the pack is unavailable in your device. Once downloaded, you have two options to translate your PDF either as a text or PDF File. Chose the relevant option. Once it is converted as a PDF, the PDF is automatically added to the PDF Manager on the second page. For text converter, you have copy option to copy the entire content to paste it whereever you want. 

### PDF Viewer

Utilize the PDF Viewer directly from our PDF Manager by simply clicking the listed PDF once. It will seamlessly transition to our fully equipped PDF Viewer with a share option. Additionally, you can employ the search bar to locate your desired PDF and open the PDF viewer. Each listed PDF file comes with a menu, allowing you to choose whether to delete the PDF or share it with others

### Bring all PDFs in one Place

By using the '+' option from our PDF Manager to bring all the PDF from your PDF to our PDF Manager to view, share and read anytime, anywhere.

